# dialogrc — vim-style key bindings for the setup.conf TUI editor.
#
# Applied via DIALOGRC env var set by script/docker/_tui_backend.sh when
# the detected backend is "dialog". whiptail ignores this file (no
# bindkey support) and falls back to stock arrow-key navigation.
#
# Syntax reference: `man dialog` → "RUN-TIME CONFIGURATION".
# Action names correspond to DLG_KEYS_ENUM entries in /usr/include/dlg_keys.h
# stripped of the `DLGK_` prefix (ITEM_NEXT, ITEM_PREV, ENTER, ESC, TOGGLE).
#
# Widget names (see `man dialog` → "Widget Names"):
#   menubox    — --menu widget (used by _tui_menu / _tui_select)
#   checklist  — --checklist widget (used by _tui_checklist)
#   radiolist  — --radiolist widget (used by _tui_radiolist)
#
# NOTE: inputbox / inputbox2 / editbox / formfield are deliberately NOT
# rebound — inside those widgets j/k/h/l must remain ordinary character
# input, otherwise the user cannot type those letters into text fields.

# ── menubox ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
bindkey menubox   j ITEM_NEXT
bindkey menubox   k ITEM_PREV
bindkey menubox   l ENTER
bindkey menubox   h ESC

# ── checklist ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# h on checklist toggles the current item (space-equivalent) rather than
# cancelling — cancelling a partially-checked list via `h` would be a
# footgun because the user would lose their other toggles.
bindkey checklist j ITEM_NEXT
bindkey checklist k ITEM_PREV
bindkey checklist l ENTER
bindkey checklist h TOGGLE

# ── radiolist ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
bindkey radiolist j ITEM_NEXT
bindkey radiolist k ITEM_PREV
bindkey radiolist l ENTER
bindkey radiolist h ESC
